# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-configuration/about-code-owners
#
# CODEOWNERS combined with "Require review from Code Owners" on the
# main branch protection rule means changes to the paths below cannot
# land without explicit owner approval. This is the last-mile defense
# against a malicious PR that tries to weaken supply-chain controls
# (e.g., loosening a cosign regex, removing an attestation step,
# changing a base image, lifting Renovate's minimumReleaseAge).
#
# Owners are listed as GitHub usernames; add additional reviewers by
# appending more @usernames separated by spaces on the same line.

# Workflow definitions and CODEOWNERS itself.
/.github/                       @enoqv

# Dockerfile + base image references.
/Dockerfile                     @enoqv
/.dockerignore                  @enoqv

# Linter and tool configuration that gates merges.
/.golangci.yml                  @enoqv
/.hadolint.yaml                 @enoqv

# Renovate config (rules that gate dependency updates).
/renovate.json                  @enoqv

# Security posture documentation -- changes here usually accompany a
# substantive policy change.
/docs/                          @enoqv
